Connect to Ubuntu EC2 Instance via SSH
    From window we need to use PuTTY:
     - Install PuTTY => https://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/
    
    Convert private key using PuTTYgen:
     - Converts PEM keys to the required PPK format for PuTTY
     - PuTTY does not natively support the PEM format for SSH keys
     - Steps:
       - Open PuTTYgen
       - Type of key to generate: choose RSA
       - Load pem key
       - Save the new ppk key!
    
    Connection to EC2 Instance:
     - Start PuTTY
     - Session:
       - instance-user-name@instance-public-dns-name
         e.g ubuntu@ec2-18-229-139-121.sa-east-1.compute.amazonaws.com
       - Port 22
       - SSH connection
     - Connection/SSH/Auth:
       - Browser => place ppk key!
    


-- Terminal  EC2
ubuntu@ip-172-31-44-178$

   